Sculptor->Mirror

"Mirror" is used to create mirrored objects, like a right hand from a
left hand. The tool brings up a mirror in the viewer window(s), close
to the object, and the mirrored object appears behind the mirror.

You can move the mirror by moving the cursor to the base of the arrow
until a green box appears. Then move the mirror while keeping the left
mouse button pressed. You can rotate the mirror by moving the cursor
to the head of the arrow until a green box appears, and moving while
keeping the left mouse button pressed.

As in other tools, the user can change the name of the new object
created.

